<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ881010-0055 </DOCNO><HL> McDermott Unit Gets $61.7 Million Contract For 3 Sonar Vessels </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MDR LK MD GE ARCE TXT BA </CO><G> DEF </G><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   McDermott Inc., a unit of McDermott International Inc., received a $61.7 million Navy contract for three sonar vessels.    Bell-Boeing Inc., a joint venture of Textron Inc. and Boeing Co., was awarded a $60 million Navy contract for full-scale development of V-22 tilt-rotor aircraft. Boeing itself received $34.2 million in Air Force contracts for aircraft and rocket-vehicle support.    Air Cargo Equipment Corp. was issued a $35.7 million Navy contract for cargo containers.    Israel Aircraft Industries Ltd. won a $21.1 million Navy contract for trainer aircraft maintenance.    Lockheed Corp. was issued a $17.8 million Air Force contract for satellite equipment.    McDonnell Douglas Corp. received $13.4 million in Navy contracts for missile support and AV-8B aircraft.    General Electric Co. got a $12 million Army contract for helicopter engines. </TEXT></DOC>